Review: Marian Rivera is no Jennifer Love-Hewitt

Movie: The Hunger Games: The Ballad of Songbirds & Snakes

Review: Albeit narratively convoluted as it wants to achieve so many things in such a little amount of time, A Very Good Girl is still a sleek and stylish revenge dark comedy boasting great performances from Ms. Bernardo and Ms. De Leon who both deliciously portrayed their characters to life.
Saw X reinvents itself by adding a surprising amount of heart to set it apart from its predecessors making it more than just your typical torture porn flick.
Talk to Me is a 21st century elevated horror with foundations from classical tropes about the unsettling nature of grief and loss.

Barbie is a delectable eye-candy of feminist fable that is a masterclass in marketing if not entirely in filmmaking. Nonetheless, Greta Gerwig still delivers a highly entertaining film with a surprising heart. Barbie is a Ken-out-of-Ken.
Watching Oppenheimer first as the main course, then Barbie as the dessert to cleanse my palette. Babrbenheimer weekend is a full plate.
Regardless of its flaws, The Flash is the perfect swan song for the DCEU.
Even I will give up my voice for Prince Erick' s D :)
